Since SkinAqua White has been less popular than the blue one, I must admit that I purchased it for my experiment to see what the differences were. I discovered that the white one is more matte, suitable for oily skin, and will work well when exposed to the sun in tropical climates. Another distinction is that after applying it to roughly two lines on each of two fingers, it turned whitecast and required 30 seconds of rubbing. Unfortunately, the white one did not work well on my combination skin (at the time); in fact, it makes my skin worse if I use it in chlorine-filled swimming pools.
